ould help ensure the default helper is used.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing API and native image requirements**\\n\\nI'm considering using a public API without direct reflection, so I'll need to set the TCCL and possibly use `System.setProperty`. Since ProjectHelper isn't abstract, I can instantiate a subclass. I wonder if parsing can default without overrides. There's also a potential issue with dynamic class loading for nested classes via `Class.forName`. Native image tests may require reachable metadata and need to run with an agent to generate it. However, existing metadata should suffice for adding tests, assuming reachability is established.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking native image metadata requirements**\\n\\nFor the native image, I need to ensure that both test sources and the generated agent metadata are included. That sounds fine. I need to be careful regarding the Security Manager, but it seems like I don't need to worry about that. I wonder if I need to inspect any test resources, but it looks like that’s not necessary either. Keeping track of these details will help me navigate the process more smoothly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_usNu95KuOFnNr7Hewc79hlmy|fc_0037ab10dfb697bf0169efd0b28f0081a3b83ac0fc84a79b93", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/resources -maxdepth 3 -type f -print 2>/dev/null || true && rg -n \"setContextClassLoader|ProjectHelper\" tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 772, "output": 1028, "cacheRead": 13312, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 15112, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777324190080, "responseId": "resp_0037ab10dfb697bf0169efd09e946c81a3b1792acdaf335b7f"}}
